Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

This is not as simple as the upstream version, is it....
And both are wrong I think.  Shouldn't it be !cap_raised... ??

Given how often it is called, it might make sense to keep a
helper function - probably static inline.

static inline const struct cred *cfs_raise_resource(void)
{
  const struct cred *cred;

  if (cap_raised(current_cap(), CAP_SYS_RESOURCE))
        return get_cred(current->cred);
  cred = prepare_creds();
  if (!cred)
        return get_cred(current->cred);
  cap_raise(cred->cap_effective, CAP_SYS_RESOURCE);
  return override_creds(cred);
}

Then a caller calls
 old_cred = cfs_raise_resource();
and does stuff, then
 revert_creds(old_cred);
with no conditional.
